column5: definition
A vein that is tributary of the main pulmonary veins and drains oxygenated blood from a segment of the lung.
A vein that is tributary of the segmental pulmonary veins and drains oxygenated blood from a subsegment of the lung.
A vein that is tributary of the azygos vein and drains blood from the esophagus.
A vein that is tributary of the superior intercostal vein and drains the first intercostal space.
An artery that branches from the right coronary artery and supplies the atrioventricular node.
column7: Atrioventricular node branch of right coronary artery

column5: A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein and drains the anterior surface of the sacrum.
A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein.
A vein that is tributary of the internal iliac vein and drains the uterus.
A vein that is tributary of a vertebral vein and drains the suboccipital region, adjacent vertebral column, and deep muscles of the neck.
An artery that is a branch of the segmental pulmonary artery and supplies deoxyge blood to a smaller subsegment of the lung.
A venule that receives drainage from the capillary beds after blood has perfused the pulmonary alveoli, and is tributary of the pulmonary venules.
An artery that branches from the subclavian artery and supplies the thyroid gland, neck, and upper back regions.
An artery that branches from the left anterior descending artery and supplies the interventricular septum of the heart.
An artery that branches from the right coronary artery or the circumflex artery and supplies the posterior and lateral walls of the left ventricle.
A vein that is tributary of the femoral vein and drains blood from the front and middle areas of the thigh.
column7: Set of lateral circumflex femoral veins

column5: A vein that is tributary of the anterior internal vertebral venous plexus and drains blood from the vertebral bodies.
A venule that is tributary of the bronchial veins and drains blood from the bronchi and bronchioles of the lungs.
A vein that is tributary of the facial vein and drains blood from the chin and lower lip.
A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the tongue.
A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the dorsum of the tongue, and the sides of the tongue.
A vein that is tributary of the lingual vein and drains blood from the ventral (inferior) surface of the tongue and the sublingual glands.
A venous plexus tha connects the middle and superior thyroid veins.
column7: glandular venous plexus of the thiroid | thiroid venous plexus

column5: A vein that is tributary of the axillary vein and drains blood from the region around the neck of the humerus.
A vein that is tributary of the axillary vein and drains blood from the thoracoacromial region, including the pectoral, shoulder, and clavicular regions.
A vein that is tributary of the external jugular vein and drains blood from the superficial muscles of the back, mainly the trapezius muscle.
A venous plexus that is tributary of the deep cervical veins and drains blood from the suboccipital region.
An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteries and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries and alveolar capillaries of the lungs.
An artery of the neck that branches from the external carotid artery and supplies the pharynx.
An artery that branches from the internal carotid artery and supplies the anterior clinoid process of the dura mater.
An artery that branches from the descending thoracic aorta and supplies the dorsal portion of the pericardium.
An artery that branches from the internal thoracic artery and supplies the pericardium and the diaphragm.
A vein that is tributary of the great saphenous vein and drains blood from the inguinal region and the anterior abdominal wall.
A vein that is tributary of the posterior tibial vein and drains blood from the lateral compartment of the leg.
A venule that is tributary of the prostatic venous plexus and drains blood from the prostate gland.

A venule that branches from the hepatic portal vein to transport nutrient-rich blood from the gastrointestinal tract and spleen to supply the liver. The hepatic portal venule is tributary of the hepatic sinusoids.
An artery that branches from the inferior alveolar artery and supplies the roots and pulp of the teeth of the lower jaw. It forms anastomoses with its contralateral partner.
A vein that is tributary of the angular vein and drains blood from the superficial tissues and skin of the dorsum (bridge) and ala (wings) of the nose.
A vein that is tributary of the angular vein and drains blood from the muscles and skin of the forehead.
A vein that is tributary of the angular veins and drains blood from the bridge of the nose.
A vein that is tributary of the cavernous sinus and drains blood from the pituitary gland.

A vein that is tributary of the transverse sinus and drains blood from the adjacent cortical regions of the temporal lobe. The inferior anastomotic vein forms an anastomosis (connection) between the superficial middle cerebral vein anteriorly and the transverse sinus posteriorly.
A vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the lateral structures of the forearm, carpal and metacarpal bones, joints of the hand, and lateral forearm muscles.
A vein that is tributary of the brachial vein and drains blood from the hand and medial and posterior aspect of forearm.
An arteriole that branches from the pulmonary arteriole and supplies deoxygenated blood to the pulmonary capillaries in the alveoli of the lungs.
An artery that branches from the facial artery, and branches to supply the soft palate and the palatine tonsil.
An artery that branches from the facial artery that runs forward under the mouth, then turns upward upon reaching the chin.

An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies blood to the tongue itself, particularly the body and tip of the tongue. The deep lingual artery travels superiorly in a tortuous course along the under (ventral) surface of the tongue, below the longitudinalis inferior, and above the mucous membrane.

An artery that branches from the lingual artery and supplies the soft palate, tonsils, epiglottis, palatoglossal arch, and adjacent mucous membrane. The dorsal lingual artery runs along the upper border of the hyoid bone and anastomises with its fellow of the opposite side.

An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the meninges. The accessory meningeal artery ascends through the foramen ovale to enter the cranial cavity and supply the dura mater of the floor of the middle cranial fossa and of the trigeminal cave, and to the trigeminal ganglion.

An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies blood to structures in the auditory tube, tympanic cavity, and upper pharynx. The artery of the pterygoid canal courses through the pterygoid canal, a small bony canal located in the sphenoid bone of the skull.
An artery that branches from the maxillary artery and supplies the hard and soft palate.
An artery that branches from the left coronary artery and supplies the anterior wall of the left ventricle, the interventricular septum, and the apex of the heart.
column7: Anterior interventricular branch of left coronary artery | anterior interventricular artery

column5: A venous plexus that is tributary of the basivertebral veins and internal vertebral veins, draining blood from the vertebrae and spinal cord. The anterior internal vertebral venous plexus is located within the vertebral canal.

A vein that drains blood from the vertebral column and intervertebral discs. In the neck, it is tributary of into the vertebral veins. In the thorax, it is tributary of the posterior intercostal veins. In the lumbar and sacral regions, it is tributary of the lumbar and lateral sacral veins
A vein that is tributary of the inferior vena cava and drains blood from the posterior abdominal wall and lumbar region.
